Document: MenuButton
Path: godot/classes/class_menubutton.rst
Summary: A button that displays a popup menu when clicked.

MenuButton

Inherits: Button < Control < CanvasItem < Node < Object

A button that displays a popup menu when clicked.

The MenuButton is a specialized Button that shows a PopupMenu when pressed. You can add items to the menu by creating PopupMenuItem nodes as children of the MenuButton, or by using the add_item method.

The popup menu is automatically managed by the MenuButton. You can access it via the get_popup method.

Signals:

item_selected(int id)
Emitted when an item in the menu is selected. The id of the selected item is passed as an argument.

Methods:

bool is_item_disabled(int id) const
Returns true if the item with the given id is disabled.

void set_item_disabled(int id, bool disabled)
Disables or enables the item with the given id.

void add_item(String text, int id = -1, int acc_key = 0, bool disabled = false, bool checked = false)
Adds an item to the menu.

void add_separator()
Adds a separator line to the menu.

void clear()
Removes all items from the menu.

int get_item_count() const
Returns the number of items in the menu.

String get_item_text(int id) const
Returns the text of the item with the given id.

int get_item_id(int idx) const
Returns the id of the item at the given index.

int get_selected_id() const
Returns the id of the currently selected item.

int get_current_index() const
Returns the index of the currently selected item.

void set_current_index(int index)
Sets the currently selected item by its index.

void set_disable_shortcuts_in_popup(bool disabled)
If true, shortcuts will not be processed when the popup is open.

Popupmenu get_popup()
Returns the PopupMenu instance used by this button.

void set_shortcut_disabled(int id, bool disabled)
Disables or enables the shortcut for the item with the given id.

bool is_shortcut_disabled(int id) const
Returns true if the shortcut for the item with the given id is disabled.

void set_item_checked(int id, bool checked)
Sets whether the item with the given id is checked.

bool is_item_checked(int id) const
Returns true if the item with the given id is checked.

void set_item_metadata(int id, Variant meta)
Sets the metadata for the item with the given id.

Variant get_item_metadata(int id) const
Returns the metadata for the item with the given id.

void set_switch_on_hover(bool enable)
If true, the button will switch to the "pressed" state when the mouse hovers over it.

bool is_switch_on_hover() const
Returns true if "switch on hover" is enabled.

void set_hide_on_item_selectable_only(bool hide)
If true, the popup will only hide if an item that is not selectable is chosen.

bool is_hide_on_item_selectable_only() const
Returns true if "hide on item selectable only" is enabled.
