Document: MenuButton
Path: godot/classes/class_menubutton.rst
Summary: A button that displays a popup menu when clicked, allowing for dynamic menu item creation.
Inherits: Button < BaseButton < Control < CanvasItem < Node < Object

A button that brings up a PopupMenu when clicked. To create new items inside this PopupMenu, use `get_popup().add_item("My Item Name")`. You can also create them directly from Godot editor's inspector.

See also BaseButton which contains common properties and methods associated with this node.
---CHUNK---
Document: MenuButton
Path: godot/classes/class_menubutton.rst
Summary: Properties of the MenuButton class, including its action mode, focus mode, and properties related to its popup menu items.

Properties:
* action_mode (ActionMode): Controls how the button reacts to clicks. Overrides BaseButton.action_mode. Default: 0.
* flat (bool): If true, the button will have no visible background. Overrides Button.flat. Default: true.
* focus_mode (FocusMode): Determines how the button receives focus. Overrides Control.focus_mode. Default: 3.
* item_count (int): The number of items in the popup menu. Default: 0.
* popup/item_{index}/checkable (int): If non-zero, the menu item at the given index is checkable. Default: 0.
* popup/item_{index}/checked (bool): If true, the menu item at the given index is checked. Default: false.
* popup/item_{index}/disabled (bool): If true, the menu item at the given index is disabled. Default: false.
* popup/item_{index}/icon (Texture2D): The icon for the menu item at the given index.
* popup/item_{index}/id (int): The ID for the menu item at the given index. Default: 0.
* popup/item_{index}/separator (bool): If true, the menu item at the given index is a separator. Default: false.
* popup/item_{index}/text (String): The text for the menu item at the given index. Default: "".
* switch_on_hover (bool): If true, the popup menu will open when the mouse hovers over the button. Default: false.
* toggle_mode (bool): If true, the button can be toggled on and off. Overrides BaseButton.toggle_mode. Default: true.
---CHUNK---
Document: MenuButton
Path: godot/classes/class_menubutton.rst
Summary: This section describes the methods available for the MenuButton class in Godot Engine.

Methods
* get_popup() → PopupMenu: Returns the PopupMenu instance used by this MenuButton.
* set_disable_shortcuts(disabled: bool): Disables the shortcuts for this MenuButton.
* show_popup(): Shows the PopupMenu for this MenuButton.

Signals
* about_to_popup(): Emitted when the PopupMenu of this MenuButton is about to show.
