Summary: Describes the properties and member variables of the MenuButton class in Godot Engine.

Property: item_count
Type: int
Default: 0
Description: The number of items currently in the list.
Setter: set_item_count(value: int)
Getter: get_item_count() -> int

Property: popup/item_{index}/checkable
Type: int
Default: 0
Description: The checkable item type of the item at index.
Note: index is a value in the 0 .. item_count - 1 range.

Property: popup/item_{index}/checked
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, the item at index is checked.
Note: index is a value in the 0 .. item_count - 1 range.

Property: popup/item_{index}/disabled
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, the item at index is disabled.
Note: index is a value in the 0 .. item_count - 1 range.

Property: popup/item_{index}/icon
Type: Texture2D
Description: The icon of the item at index.
Note: index is a value in the 0 .. item_count - 1 range.

Property: popup/item_{index}/id
Type: int
Default: 0
Description: The ID of the item at index.
Note: index is a value in the 0 .. item_count - 1 range.

Property: popup/item_{index}/separator
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, the item at index is a separator.
Note: index is a value in the 0 .. item_count - 1 range.

Property: popup/item_{index}/text
Type: String
Default: ""
Description: The text of the item at index.
Note: index is a value in the 0 .. item_count - 1 range.

Property: switch_on_hover
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, when the cursor hovers above another MenuButton within the same parent which also has switch_on_hover enabled, it will close the current MenuButton and open the other one.
Setter: set_switch_on_hover(value: bool)
Getter: is_switch_on_hover() -> bool
